# ===========================================================================
%NAME Samples1: use context variable in queries
# ===========================================================================
%DESCRIPTION
# ??????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????
VDP query checked against direct data-source query, this time declaring a
context by means of the "%CONTEXT" directive, which allows us to specify a
series of properties that can be used in the value of any other directive
(like e.g. %EXECUTION or %RESULTS in these cases).

The format of the %CONTEXT directive is exactly equivalent to that of Java's
".properties" files (read by the java.util.Properties class).
# ===========================================================================
%CONTEXT
namevar = PENELOPE
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
%EXECUTION[query]
{ ds:vdp }
SELECT first_name,last_name
FROM sakila_actor
WHERE first_name = '${namevar}'
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
%RESULTS[query]
{
  ds:sakila,
  ordered:no
}
SELECT first_name,last_name
FROM actor
WHERE first_name = '${namevar}'
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
